                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-11-person136">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ROSSER
               <interp inst="t18170917-11-person136" type="surname" value="ROSSER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person136" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person136" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to John Williams, who is a <rs id="t18170917-11-viclabel60" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-11-victim135 t18170917-11-viclabel60"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18170917-11-crimeloc61">Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-11-crimeloc61" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-11-crimeloc61" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-11-off58 t18170917-11-crimeloc61"></join>. On the 13th of September, between seven and eight o'clock in the evening, the shawl hung on the rail by the side of the window; I saw the prisoner running with it in his hands - I secured him, and never lost sight of him. He threw the shawl away-it was picked up by Barrington.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-11-person137">
                  THOMAS 
                  THOMAS
               <interp inst="t18170917-11-person137" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person137" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person137" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the shop, close to the window, while I was opening a drawer the shawl was taken; the prisoner was brought back with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-11-person138">
                  JOHN 
                  GOODWIN
               <interp inst="t18170917-11-person138" type="surname" value="GOODWIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person138" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person138" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was passing by, and saw the prisoner with several others; the prisoner turned round to see if any person was looking, then darted in, took the shawl, and ran off - I collared him, and he threw it away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-11-person139">
                  RICHARD 
                  BARRINGTON
               <interp inst="t18170917-11-person139" type="surname" value="BARRINGTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person139" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-11-person139" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going into a grocer's shop next door to Mr. Williams's, and picked up the shawl by the door.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
